<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Connecticut State Library, Hartford ]">Ct</span>: Trumbull Papers.
 Wording for the mutilated portions of the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr> is taken from the letter-book copy.</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-03-02-pb-0489">[489]</span>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0360-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0360-fn-0001">1</a>
	
   <p>For GWs request for volunteers from Connecticut to accompany Gen. Charles Lee to New York, see his <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0031" class="document">letter to Trumbull of 7 Jan. 1776</a>. See also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0069" class="document">Trumbull to GW, 15 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0360-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0360-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Trumbull and the council of safety met in a special session on this date and approved these orders to the commanding officers of certain specified militia regiments. See <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Royal R. Hinman, comp. &lt;i&gt;A Historical Collection, from Official Records, Files &amp;amp;c., of the Part Sustained by Connecticut, during the War of the Revolution&lt;/i&gt;. Hartford, 1842. ]">Hinman, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Historical Collection</span></span>, 34950.</p>

</div>
